dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Grodno, sheet L-18. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Grodno, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 and Russian belt 5 grids. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 34-37, 1929; 34-38, 1930; 35-37, 1928 and 35-38, 1932. Road classification based on British intelligence reports, 1943. Map states location as Poland though the map actually depicts Belarus.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
